WEBVTT

00:00:37.625 --> 00:00:40.458
Well? You want to fight too?

00:00:40.875 --> 00:00:46.167
I'll pass. My magic skill will reach 900 soon.
I don't want a death penalty.

00:00:46.167 --> 00:00:49.750
You're an honest one...
What about you, Miss?

00:00:51.333 --> 00:00:55.292
I'm good too.
Next time, I'll win.

00:00:55.292 --> 00:00:58.958
I'd prefer not to
fight you one-on-one.

00:01:03.625 --> 00:01:09.000
<i>The feelings I've hidden</i>
<i>are crying out in pain</i>

00:01:09.000 --> 00:01:14.625
<i>Holding a sure promise in my hand</i>

00:01:24.833 --> 00:01:35.125
<i>Seeking only a miracle, I wander</i>
<i>through an endless darkness</i>

00:01:35.292 --> 00:01:45.833
<i>If I stay here, I won't</i>
<i>ever see the future again</i>

00:01:45.958 --> 00:01:51.125
<i>Tonight the moon summons me again.</i>
<i>Though I still cannot speak,</i>

00:01:51.125 --> 00:01:54.917
<i>I keep crying out in my heart</i>

00:01:56.042 --> 00:02:01.292
<i>My hidden feelings</i>
<i>are crying out in pain</i>

00:02:01.542 --> 00:02:06.458
<i>Holding a sure promise in my hand</i>

00:02:06.625 --> 00:02:12.167
<i>If I can stay stronger a bit longer,</i>

00:02:12.167 --> 00:02:18.250
<i>I will go beyond</i>
<i>this sky right in front of me</i>

00:02:20.083 --> 00:02:26.667
<i>I will reach out towards</i>
<i>the future ahead of me</i>

00:02:32.000 --> 00:02:36.000
"Captive Queen"

00:02:36.708 --> 00:02:40.417
--Hey, what are these flames?
--Shh... Remain Lights.

00:02:40.417 --> 00:02:43.042
Their minds are still there.

00:02:46.167 --> 00:02:48.917
So, what should I do now?

00:02:48.917 --> 00:02:51.375
Thank you? Run away?

00:02:52.125 --> 00:02:54.333
Or should I fight?

00:02:54.958 --> 00:03:00.500
Personally, I see this as the scene where
the knight of justice saved the princess.

00:03:00.625 --> 00:03:03.667
And she weeps and
runs into his arms.

00:03:03.667 --> 00:03:06.042
Are you an idiot?

00:03:06.042 --> 00:03:08.042
I was kidding!

00:03:08.792 --> 00:03:10.042
That's right!

00:03:10.042 --> 00:03:13.875
--You can't do that!
--Hey, stay out of sight...

00:03:13.875 --> 00:03:17.083
Only Mommy and I can hug Daddy!

00:03:17.083 --> 00:03:18.500
D-Daddy?

00:03:18.500 --> 00:03:20.958
Oh... Well, this is...

00:03:21.542 --> 00:03:25.167
Hey, is that a private pixie?

00:03:25.458 --> 00:03:28.667
Y-Yeah, something like that.

00:03:30.125 --> 00:03:34.292
Fine, but why is a Spriggan
wandering around here?

00:03:35.125 --> 00:03:37.333
I-I got lost...

00:03:40.750 --> 00:03:46.458
Your territory is way to the east!
How can you be that lost? You're so weird.

00:03:52.250 --> 00:03:56.083
Anyway, I should thank you.
Thanks for saving me.

00:03:56.083 --> 00:03:58.125
My name's Leafa.

00:03:58.125 --> 00:04:00.875
I'm Kirito. This is Yui.

00:04:05.958 --> 00:04:08.750
So, Kirito...

00:04:08.750 --> 00:04:14.625
What'll you do now? If you'd like,
I could buy you a drink as thanks. Well?

00:04:14.625 --> 00:04:19.500
That'd be nice. Actually, I was looking for
someone who could explain a few things.

00:04:19.500 --> 00:04:20.958
Like what?

00:04:20.958 --> 00:04:26.083
About this world, and about
that tree in particular.

00:04:26.083 --> 00:04:28.833
That tree? The World Tree?

00:04:29.583 --> 00:04:33.750
Sure. I may not look like one,
but I'm quite a veteran.

00:04:34.500 --> 00:04:39.583
Okay, it's a bit far, but there's a neutral
village up north. Let's fly there.

00:04:39.583 --> 00:04:42.958
Huh? Isn't the town
called Sylvain closer?

00:04:44.333 --> 00:04:46.583
You really are clueless.

00:04:46.583 --> 00:04:49.417
--That's Sylph territory.
--So?

00:04:49.417 --> 00:04:54.625
You can't attack Sylphs in their territory,
but they can attack you.

00:04:55.875 --> 00:05:01.458
They wouldn't just start attacking.
And I have you with me, Miss Leafa.

00:05:02.250 --> 00:05:08.833
Call me Leafa. If you insist, it's fine.
But I can't guarantee you'll survive.

00:05:09.375 --> 00:05:11.792
All right, let's fly then.

00:05:14.458 --> 00:05:18.083
Huh? You can fly
without an assist controller?

00:05:18.083 --> 00:05:23.833
--Well, yeah. What about you?
--I just recently learned how to use this...

00:05:23.833 --> 00:05:29.125
There's a trick to manual flying.
Turn around and don't use the controller.

00:05:29.125 --> 00:05:30.583
O-Okay.

00:05:32.000 --> 00:05:34.625
Can you feel where I'm touching?

00:05:34.625 --> 00:05:39.875
Imagine virtual bones and muscles
spreading from here and move them.

00:05:39.875 --> 00:05:42.583
Virtual bones and muscles...

00:05:44.625 --> 00:05:46.042
That's right!

00:05:47.208 --> 00:05:48.833
Keep that up.

00:05:48.833 --> 00:05:52.208
Try the same movement again,
but stronger.

00:06:07.333 --> 00:06:08.750
Oh, crap!

00:06:08.750 --> 00:06:11.708
--Daddy!
--Kirito, you okay?

00:06:19.208 --> 00:06:22.208
Make it stop!

00:06:25.667 --> 00:06:29.333
I'm sorry, Daddy! That's hilarious...

00:06:38.167 --> 00:06:39.792
This is great.

00:06:40.208 --> 00:06:42.333
It is, isn't it?

00:06:42.333 --> 00:06:45.000
You've got good instincts.

00:06:45.000 --> 00:06:47.542
--Now, follow me.
--Okay.

00:06:48.208 --> 00:06:51.125
You can take it slow at first.

00:06:52.333 --> 00:06:54.375
We can go faster.

00:07:08.875 --> 00:07:11.375
Is this the fastest you can go?

00:07:11.375 --> 00:07:14.417
Don't blame me
for whatever happens.

00:07:25.542 --> 00:07:27.917
I can't go on...

00:07:35.958 --> 00:07:40.667
You might be the only other person
who can handle this speed.

00:07:41.750 --> 00:07:44.458
"Sylph Territory, Sylvain
January 20, 2025"

00:07:48.042 --> 00:07:49.542
We're here.

00:07:50.333 --> 00:07:53.583
We'll land at the base
of the central tower.

00:07:53.583 --> 00:07:57.500
Wait, Kirito, do you
know how to land?

00:07:58.875 --> 00:08:01.625
--I have no idea...
--Um...

00:08:02.417 --> 00:08:05.167
Sorry! It's too late.

00:08:05.167 --> 00:08:06.542
Good luck!

00:08:06.542 --> 00:08:09.333
Y-You're kidding me!

00:08:17.208 --> 00:08:22.250
--That was horrible, Leafa.
--It's okay. I'll heal you.

00:08:28.958 --> 00:08:31.833
Wow, so this is magic?

00:08:31.833 --> 00:08:36.917
Only Undines can use high-level healing magic,
but this one's an important spell,

00:08:36.917 --> 00:08:38.750
so you should learn it too.

00:08:38.750 --> 00:08:42.333
Different races
get different bonuses?

00:08:42.333 --> 00:08:45.292
What are Spriggans good at?

00:08:45.292 --> 00:08:48.542
Treasure hunting and
illusion magic, I guess.

00:08:48.542 --> 00:08:52.042
Neither of those
is much use in battle.

00:08:58.875 --> 00:09:01.542
So this is a Sylph town?

00:09:01.542 --> 00:09:03.333
It's pretty.

00:09:03.542 --> 00:09:05.250
Isn't it?

00:09:05.250 --> 00:09:07.250
Leafa!

00:09:07.708 --> 00:09:09.750
You're okay!

00:09:09.750 --> 00:09:11.375
Oh, Recon.

00:09:12.250 --> 00:09:14.167
I knew you'd survive.

00:09:14.167 --> 00:09:15.875
A Spriggan?

00:09:17.375 --> 00:09:19.917
It's okay. He saved me.

00:09:21.292 --> 00:09:24.167
This is Recon, my friend.

00:09:24.167 --> 00:09:26.292
Hi, I'm Kirito.

00:09:26.292 --> 00:09:28.625
Nice to meet you.

00:09:29.708 --> 00:09:32.500
No... No no no!
I take that back!

00:09:32.500 --> 00:09:35.875
Are you sure about this?
He's not some spy, is he?

00:09:35.875 --> 00:09:37.500
It's fine.

00:09:37.500 --> 00:09:41.083
He's a little too dim to be a spy.

00:09:41.083 --> 00:09:42.583
That's mean.

00:09:42.583 --> 00:09:46.083
Sigurd and the rest
saved us seats at our usual bar.

00:09:46.083 --> 00:09:47.333
Okay.

00:09:50.250 --> 00:09:52.167
I'll pass today.

00:09:52.167 --> 00:09:54.375
Huh? You're not coming?

00:09:54.375 --> 00:09:58.750
No, I promised Kirito
a drink for saving me.

00:09:58.750 --> 00:10:01.167
--See you later!
--W-Wait...

00:10:02.917 --> 00:10:04.875
Leafa...

00:10:16.833 --> 00:10:20.792
--Was that your boyfriend?
--Your lover?

00:10:21.250 --> 00:10:25.167
N-No! He's a party member.
That's all.

00:10:25.167 --> 00:10:27.958
You seemed pretty close, though.

00:10:27.958 --> 00:10:31.333
I know him in real life.
He's my classmate.

00:10:31.333 --> 00:10:33.333
But that's all it is!

00:10:36.750 --> 00:10:40.667
Anyway, once again,
thanks for saving me!

00:10:44.917 --> 00:10:49.917
They were really aggressive...
Are group PKs like that common?

00:10:50.250 --> 00:10:53.625
Salamanders and Sylphs
are opposed by nature.

00:10:53.625 --> 00:10:57.792
But an organized PK like that
is pretty new.

00:10:57.792 --> 00:11:02.333
I'm sure they'll start trying
to clear the World Tree soon.

00:11:02.333 --> 00:11:05.750
I'd like you to tell me
about that.

00:11:05.750 --> 00:11:09.417
Right, you did mention that.
But why?

00:11:09.417 --> 00:11:12.708
I want to get to
the World Tree's top.

00:11:12.708 --> 00:11:16.042
I think that's true for
all the players.

00:11:16.042 --> 00:11:20.875
--Actually, that's ALO's Grand Quest.
--What do you mean?

00:11:20.875 --> 00:11:23.583
You know about the limit
on flight time.

00:11:23.583 --> 00:11:28.208
And no race can fly continuously
for more than 10 minutes.

00:11:28.208 --> 00:11:33.292
But the first race to reach the Floating City
atop the World Tree and hold audience

00:11:33.292 --> 00:11:39.625
with the fairy king Oberon will be reborn
as an advanced class called Alfs.

00:11:39.917 --> 00:11:44.208
And they'll be able
to fly as much as they like.

00:11:44.208 --> 00:11:47.875
I see. That does sound nice.

00:11:49.708 --> 00:11:52.500
How do you get to the top?

00:11:52.500 --> 00:11:57.417
The base is a big dome. You can
reach the Floating City from there.

00:11:57.417 --> 00:12:02.458
But the NPC guardians that
defend the dome are really powerful.

00:12:02.458 --> 00:12:05.708
--That strong?
--The game's a year old.

00:12:05.708 --> 00:12:09.208
Would you believe
no one's beaten the quest?

00:12:09.208 --> 00:12:12.833
Everyone must be
missing a key quest. Or...

00:12:12.833 --> 00:12:17.000
It's set so one race can't
get there by themselves.

00:12:17.000 --> 00:12:19.375
You have good instincts.

00:12:19.375 --> 00:12:23.500
Everyone's searching like mad
now for a missed quest.

00:12:23.500 --> 00:12:27.125
But if it's the latter,
no one will clear it.

00:12:27.125 --> 00:12:28.583
No one?

00:12:28.583 --> 00:12:33.875
Because it makes no sense.
If only one race can clear it,

00:12:33.875 --> 00:12:37.708
why would you help
another race?

00:12:37.708 --> 00:12:42.875
Then does that mean it's impossible
to reach the top of the World Tree?

00:12:43.667 --> 00:12:48.542
I think so. But you
can't just give it up.

00:12:48.542 --> 00:12:54.083
Not once you see how fun flying is.
Even if it takes years, I'm sure...

00:12:54.083 --> 00:12:56.458
I can't wait that long!

00:13:02.750 --> 00:13:03.958
Daddy?

00:13:05.417 --> 00:13:10.500
I'm sorry. But I need to reach
the top of the World Tree.

00:13:12.958 --> 00:13:17.958
--Why is it so important?
--I'm looking for someone.

00:13:17.958 --> 00:13:23.042
--What do you mean?
--It's not easy to explain.

00:13:29.500 --> 00:13:34.125
Thank you, Leafa. All that
information helped me a lot.

00:13:39.875 --> 00:13:44.292
Wait. Are you going
to the World Tree?

00:13:44.292 --> 00:13:48.000
Yes, I need to see for myself.

00:13:49.167 --> 00:13:51.667
But that's crazy.

00:13:52.083 --> 00:13:56.208
It's really far, and there
are a lot of strong monsters.

00:13:56.208 --> 00:13:58.750
Sure, you're strong, but...

00:14:01.292 --> 00:14:04.458
All right, I'll take you there!

00:14:07.708 --> 00:14:11.667
But I couldn't ask that
of someone I just met.

00:14:11.833 --> 00:14:17.333
Do you know how to get there?
What'll you do about the guardians?

00:14:17.333 --> 00:14:19.792
Well, I'll think of something.

00:14:20.417 --> 00:14:24.125
It's fine. I've already
made up my mind!

00:14:25.750 --> 00:14:26.917
Fine.

00:14:27.458 --> 00:14:30.917
Um... Can you log in tomorrow?

00:14:31.167 --> 00:14:32.500
Y-Yeah.

00:14:32.500 --> 00:14:36.542
Then be here at 3:00 PM.
I have to log off.

00:14:36.542 --> 00:14:40.750
Use the rooms upstairs to log out.
Well, till tomorrow...

00:14:40.750 --> 00:14:42.167
Wait.

00:14:46.167 --> 00:14:47.458
Thank you.

00:15:10.583 --> 00:15:13.083
All right, I'll take you there!

00:15:22.500 --> 00:15:25.083
He was a weird guy...

00:15:26.375 --> 00:15:28.458
Kirito, huh?

00:15:38.208 --> 00:15:41.375
It's goodbye till tomorrow, Daddy.

00:15:41.375 --> 00:15:44.958
I'll be back soon, to see you.

00:15:46.208 --> 00:15:47.417
Um...

00:15:48.208 --> 00:15:53.000
Can I sleep next to you
until you log out, Daddy?

00:15:55.500 --> 00:15:57.333
Yeah, sure.

00:16:03.708 --> 00:16:09.125
Let's save Asuna and buy
a house somewhere again, okay?

00:16:09.125 --> 00:16:14.875
It sounds like a dream,
living with you and Mommy again.

00:16:18.208 --> 00:16:22.250
It isn't a dream.
I'll make it real soon.

00:16:33.917 --> 00:16:36.667
Good night, Daddy.

00:17:04.917 --> 00:17:09.333
That look on your face
is just the loveliest, Titania.

00:17:09.333 --> 00:17:16.000
The one where you seem about to cry.
I want to freeze it and hang it on a wall.

00:17:16.125 --> 00:17:18.125
Then go ahead.

00:17:26.542 --> 00:17:31.667
You can do whatever you like, right?
You're a system admin, after all.

00:17:31.667 --> 00:17:34.292
Saying such cold things again.

00:17:34.292 --> 00:17:38.583
Have I ever forcibly laid
a finger on you, Titania?

00:17:38.917 --> 00:17:44.000
Stop calling me that weird name.
My name is Asuna, Sugou.

00:17:45.667 --> 00:17:50.125
You're ruining the fun... In this world,
I'm the fairy king, Oberon.

00:17:50.125 --> 00:17:54.417
The ruler of ALfheim,
who all players regard with envy.

00:17:54.417 --> 00:17:58.042
And you're my bride,
the queen, Titania.

00:17:58.042 --> 00:18:00.208
Isn't that enough?

00:18:00.208 --> 00:18:05.083
When will you open your heart
to me as my bride?

00:18:05.792 --> 00:18:10.917
It's hopeless. Disgust and hatred
are all I have to offer you.

00:18:10.917 --> 00:18:14.542
You're very strong-willed.
But you know...

00:18:15.792 --> 00:18:21.750
Lately, I've been thinking
it might be enjoyable to take you

00:18:22.458 --> 00:18:24.750
by force.

00:18:49.667 --> 00:18:51.083
Stop it...

00:18:56.083 --> 00:19:01.000
It was a joke. I told you
I won't force myself on you.

00:19:01.000 --> 00:19:05.667
It won't be too long
before you start to want me.

00:19:06.667 --> 00:19:08.583
Are you insane?

00:19:09.333 --> 00:19:12.875
You won't be talking like that for long.

00:19:13.792 --> 00:19:19.292
In this world now, there are tens of
thousands of players enjoying the game.

00:19:19.292 --> 00:19:24.792
But they don't understand the
true value of the full-dive system.

00:19:25.917 --> 00:19:28.833
By expanding
the brain's control regions,

00:19:28.833 --> 00:19:33.167
it's possible to control thought,
emotion, and even memory.

00:19:34.333 --> 00:19:37.167
No, they wouldn't allow that...

00:19:37.167 --> 00:19:43.083
Who wouldn't allow it? Many nations
are already researching it.

00:19:43.083 --> 00:19:47.500
That said, human experiments
aren't easy to perform.

00:19:47.500 --> 00:19:52.250
But one day, I was watching the news,
and there they were.

00:19:52.250 --> 00:19:55.875
Ten thousand ideal test subjects!

00:19:57.375 --> 00:20:00.958
Mr. Kayaba was a genius,
but a fool

00:20:00.958 --> 00:20:06.542
to prepare such a splendid vessel and
just be satisfied creating a game world.

00:20:07.083 --> 00:20:09.458
It wasn't hard at all

00:20:09.458 --> 00:20:14.917
to adjust the routers to grab a few players
the instant they were released.

00:20:14.917 --> 00:20:22.542
As a result, I got 300 subjects. My research
made great strides in just two months.

00:20:22.542 --> 00:20:25.417
The technology to implant
new objects into human memories

00:20:25.417 --> 00:20:31.417
and use them to induce emotion
is more or less complete.

00:20:31.708 --> 00:20:36.875
Don't be ridiculous. My father would
never allow research like that!

00:20:39.333 --> 00:20:44.750
The research is being conducted in secret
by a very small team and me.

00:20:44.750 --> 00:20:48.833
--I couldn't sell it otherwise.
--Sell it?

00:20:48.833 --> 00:20:53.458
An American corporation is
eagerly awaiting its completion.

00:20:53.458 --> 00:20:57.958
I'm going to sell it at a high price.
And RCT too, someday.

00:20:57.958 --> 00:21:00.500
I won't let that happen.

00:21:01.208 --> 00:21:06.875
Once I return to the real world, the first
thing I'll do is report your misdeeds.

00:21:08.333 --> 00:21:12.750
You're in the same position
as the other subjects.

00:21:12.750 --> 00:21:17.417
If I wanted, I could
alter your memories too.

00:21:26.667 --> 00:21:30.000
I'm on my way.
Wait for my orders.

00:21:30.417 --> 00:21:35.500
Still, I don't want to turn you
into a mere doll.

00:21:36.000 --> 00:21:38.958
I hope you're a little more

00:21:38.958 --> 00:21:43.042
submissive the next time
we meet, Titania.

00:21:58.542 --> 00:22:00.667
Farewell, then.

00:22:13.458 --> 00:22:16.375
Save me, Kirito...

00:22:17.958 --> 00:22:25.042
<i>Higher and higher,</i>
<i>I reach out my arms</i>

00:22:25.042 --> 00:22:34.875
<i>"Surely, surely..."</i>
<i>I'll wish for it once again</i>

00:22:46.042 --> 00:22:52.917
<i>These endless feelings were</i>
<i>swallowed up into my daily life</i>

00:22:53.292 --> 00:22:59.958
<i>Swaying as they</i>
<i>change shape yet again</i>

00:23:00.458 --> 00:23:07.500
<i>Is it too late now? I ask</i>
<i>myself but receive no answer</i>

00:23:07.500 --> 00:23:15.208
<i>It's all up to me now,</i>
<i>both the ending and the beginning</i>

00:23:15.208 --> 00:23:22.125
<i>Higher and higher,</i>
<i>I reach out my arms</i>

00:23:22.125 --> 00:23:29.250
<i>I'm going to spread my wings</i>
<i>and head towards that gentle light</i>

00:23:29.250 --> 00:23:36.750
<i>Carrying the passion</i>
<i>I've lit in my heart</i>

00:23:36.750 --> 00:23:45.000
<i>"Surely, surely..."</i>
<i>I'll wish for it once again</i>

00:23:47.083 --> 00:23:53.195
Next Time: "To the World Tree."
